---
export const prerender = true;
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Embed Demo — Derby Strong Widget</title>
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
      background: #f5f5f5;
      color: #333;
    }
    .demo-page {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 3rem 1.5rem 6rem;
    }
    h1 { font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    p { color: #666; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    pre {
      background: #1e293b;
      color: #e2e8f0;
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      overflow-x: auto;
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    code { font-family: 'SF Mono', Monaco, monospace; }
    .demo-card {
      background: #fff;
      border: 1px solid #e2e5ea;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }
    .demo-card h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="demo-page">
    <h1>Widget Embed Demo</h1>
    <p>This page simulates a third-party website. The "Instant Quote" button in the bottom-right corner is loaded via the embed script.</p>

    <div class="demo-card">
      <h2>How to embed on your website</h2>
      <p>Add this single line before the closing <code>&lt;/body&gt;</code> tag:</p>
      <pre><code>&lt;script src="https://your-widget-domain.com/api/embed" async&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
      <p>That's it. The script handles everything: trigger button, panel loading, nudge tooltip, and mobile responsiveness.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="demo-card">
      <h2>Performance</h2>
      <p><strong>LCP impact: Minimal.</strong> The embed script is loaded with <code>async</code> so it never blocks page rendering. The trigger button is injected into native DOM (not an iframe), so it renders instantly. The widget panel iframe is only created on first click (lazy loaded).</p>
      <p><strong>SEO impact: None.</strong> The widget is a UI overlay — it doesn't interfere with page content, headings, or structured data. The trigger button uses semantic HTML with proper ARIA labels.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="demo-card">
      <h2>What the embed loads</h2>
      <p>1. <strong>Trigger button</strong> — 0.5KB of inline CSS + native DOM button (instant render)</p>
      <p>2. <strong>Nudge tooltip</strong> — shows after 8 seconds, once per session</p>
      <p>3. <strong>Widget panel</strong> — loaded in iframe only when user clicks (lazy, ~50KB)</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- This is the embed script — exactly what a host site would add -->
  <script src="/api/embed" async></script>
</body>
</html>
